// Smart Money Concepts [v15.4]
// Based on v12.2 — (c) LuxAlgo CC BY-NC-SA 4.0
// v12   — Pivot Source toggle, OB tolerance >2, Liquidity Sweeps
// v12.1 — Trailing extreme fix (strict >/< ), simultaneous cross safe silence
// v12.2 — Breaker Blocks (mitigated OBs convert with flipped bias)
// v13.0 — Kill Zones, Session Boxes, Previous Day/Week Levels
// v13.1 — MSS, Displacement Candles, Asian Range
// v14.0 — OTE Zone, OB Touch Count, iFVG, NDOG/NWOG, CE Midlines (OB/BB)
// v14.1 — iFVG static boxes, NDOG confirmed mitigation, OB text clear fix, touch bar skip, weekly security merge
// v14.2 — NDOG age expiry (hours-based), NDOG/NWOG confirmed-bar creation, FVG/iFVG CE lines removed, NWOG never age-expires
// v15.0 — FVG duplication fix, OTE degenerate cleanup, Asian range reset fix, Midnight Open, Silver Bullet windows
// v15.1 — OB touch count edge-detection fix (outside→inside transition only)
// v15.2 — OB touch count: wasInside default flipped to TRUE so the OB candle
//         and its immediate follow-through are no longer miscounted as "1x".
//         Touch detection now reuses the SAME mitigation source predicate that
//         deleteOrderBlocks() uses, keeping touch counting and OB removal in
//         sync under both CLOSE and HIGH/LOW mitigation modes. Breaker
//         conversion seeds wasInside = true to avoid phantom 1x on flip.
// v15.3 — Verified bug-fix release:
//         • Bearish OTE zone now anchored from swing bottom (premium half) — was
//           previously drawn in the discount half regardless of trend direction.
//           Same fix applied to the OTE-touch alert at the bottom of the script.
//         • OTE zone is no longer drawn before the first BOS/CHoCH (bias == 0).
//         • updateTrailingExtremes() now honours `pivotSourceInput` (Wick vs
//           Body), keeping Strong/Weak H/L, Premium/Discount, and OTE consistent
//           with swing pivot detection.
//         • leg() guards bars where `bar_index < 2 * size` to prevent vacuous
//           left-side pivot confirmation on the first warm-up bars.
//         • storeOrderBlock() now back-fills `touchCount` for the historical gap
//           between the OB candle (parsedIndex) and the detection bar, so the
//           first user-visible "1x" reflects real retests, not the first
//           post-detection retest.
//         • Breaker Blocks now have full touch counting (parity with OBs) via
//           updateBreakerBlockTouches(); BB creation bar is skipped to avoid
//           phantom-mitigation gap-death immediately after conversion.
//         • PDH / PDL alerts now latch on first touch (edge-detected with [1]),
//           matching the Asian/London/NY-range alert style.
//         • Float equality on pivot snap levels replaced with mintick tolerance.
//         • barDeltaPercent corrected from delta/(open*100) to delta/open*100.
//         • htfBarDuration request.security() switched to lookahead_off.
// v15.4 — Remaining bug-fix release:
//         • OB execution order: deleteOrderBlocks() now runs BEFORE
//           updateOrderBlockTouches(). Previously, on the bar of mitigation
//           an OB could be exhausted by touch counting before
//           deleteOrderBlocks() had a chance to convert it to a BB.
//         • getStyle() now has a default branch returning line.style_solid,
//           preventing na returns on unmatched strings.
//         • `varip` currentBarIndex/lastBarIndex initialised to -1 so that
//           newBar is correctly true on the first realtime bar.
//         • BB touch count display now has its own toggle
//           (showBBTouchCountInput), separate from OB touch count.
//         • New 'Body' OB mitigation mode (now the default). Under the old
//           'High/Low' mode, a 1-tick wick above an OB level triggered
//           mitigation — in ICT terms that is a liquidity sweep, not a
//           proper mitigation. 'Body' requires math.max(open,close) to clear
//           the bearish OB top / math.min(open,close) to clear the bullish
//           OB bottom, filtering micro-wick false mitigations.
// v16.0 — Major fix release:
//         • FVG body-based mitigation fixes wick false-mitigations.
//         • BB mitigation execution order fixed to allow alerts.
//         • Timezones separated for ranges.
//         • Min penetration ticks instead of pips.
//         • iFVG creation guard prevents instant deletion.
// v16.5 — Fixes OB/BB min-penetration touch parity, BB immediate gap-through
//         guard, MSS offset markers, MSS/CHoCH double alerts, range touch alert
//         timing, stale OB/BB text, first-bar division guards, independent iFVG
//         mitigation, and hidden FVG tracking for iFVG-only mode.
// v16.6 — Replaces MSS displacement plotshape offset markers with label markers
//         so the script stays below TradingView's 64-plot hard limit.
// v16.9 — Code-quality cleanup release:
//         • Replaced the 10-branch hardcoded `low[N]` / `high[N]` ladder for
//           MSS displacement label placement with native Pine v6 dynamic
//           series indexing (`low[displacementBullOffset]`). The ladder
//           silently capped any offset > 8 to N=9; harmless under the
//           current maxval=10 input cap, but a future-bump foot-gun.
//         • pushBounded() history-array writes now gated behind a single
//           `needHistoryArrays` flag (OB tracking OR MTF level drawing).
//           When all consumers are off, the eight 5000-entry float/int
//           ring buffers no longer accumulate per bar.
// v16.8 — Follow-up bug-fix release:
//         • New "OB Formed" alerts (Internal/Swing × Bullish/Bearish). The
//           legacy *OrderBlock alerts only fired on mitigation despite their
//           "Breakout" naming, leaving no way to alert on OB creation. The
//           legacy alerts are unchanged for backward compat; their messages
//           now say "mitigated" instead of "broke" for clarity.
//         • NDOG / NWOG no longer evaluated for fill on the same bar they
//           are created. The legacy close[1]-vs-gap.bottom traversal check
//           referenced close[1] from BEFORE the gap existed, occasionally
//           killing newly-formed gaps instantly on the rollover bar.
//         • Internal Order Block border colour now matches Breaker Block
//           behaviour (visible border) instead of being na, fixing a
//           cosmetic asymmetry where internal OBs looked "borderless" while
//           internal BBs always rendered with a border.
// v16.7 — Bug-fix release:
//         • Liquidity sweep now uses actual wick high/low of the swing pivot
//           bar instead of the body-source level. Fixes phantom sweeps when
//           Pivot Source = Body (any wick over the body was incorrectly
//           registering as a sweep).
//         • PDH/PDL/Midnight Open touch alerts no longer misfire on day
//           rollover. Edge-detection now requires the level itself to be
//           unchanged from the previous bar (filters spurious triggers when
//           pdHigh/midnightOpenPrice jumps to a new value).
//         • iFVG box construction normalised with math.max/min so the two
//           halves render in a deterministic top/bottom order regardless of
//           which parent FVG bias produced them.
//         • Auto-disables Kill Zones, Session Boxes, and Silver Bullet windows
//           on equity instruments (stock, fund, dr, ietf) since session-based
//           ICT timing is designed for FX/futures/crypto, not stocks.

//@version=6
indicator('Smart Money Concepts [v16.9]', 'SMC v16.9', overlay = true, max_labels_count = 500, max_lines_count = 500, max_boxes_count = 500)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Constants
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BULLISH_LEG  = 1
BEARISH_LEG  = 0
BULLISH      = +1
BEARISH      = -1
GREEN        = #089981
RED          = #F23645
BLUE         = #2157f3
GRAY         = #878b94
MONO_BULLISH = #b2b5be
MONO_BEARISH = #5d606b
HISTORICAL   = 'Historical'
PRESENT      = 'Present'
COLORED      = 'Colored'
MONOCHROME   = 'Monochrome'
ALL          = 'All'
BOS          = 'BOS'
CHOCH        = 'CHoCH'
MSS          = 'MSS'
TINY         = size.tiny
SMALL        = size.small
NORMAL       = size.normal
ATR          = 'Atr'
RANGE        = 'Cumulative Mean Range'
CLOSE_SRC    = 'Close'
BODY_SRC     = 'Body'
HIGHLOW      = 'High/Low'
SOLID        = 'Solid'
DASHED       = 'Dashed'
DOTTED       = 'Dotted'
FULL_CANDLE  = 'Full Candle'
BODY_ONLY    = 'Body Only'

SMART_GROUP    = 'Smart Money Concepts'
INTERNAL_GROUP = 'Real Time Internal Structure'
SWING_GROUP    = 'Real Time Swing Structure'
BLOCKS_GROUP   = 'Order Blocks'
BREAKER_GROUP  = 'Breaker Blocks'
EQUAL_GROUP    = 'EQH/EQL'
GAPS_GROUP     = 'Fair Value Gaps'
LEVELS_GROUP   = 'Highs & Lows MTF'
ZONES_GROUP    = 'Premium & Discount Zones'
SWEEP_GROUP    = 'Liquidity Sweeps'
MSS_GROUP      = 'Market Structure Shift'
OTE_GROUP      = 'Optimal Trade Entry'
IFVG_GROUP     = 'Inverted Fair Value Gaps'
ASIANRANGE_GROUP = 'Asian Range'
KILLZONE_GROUP = 'Kill Zones'
SESSION_GROUP  = 'Sessions'
PDHL_GROUP     = 'Previous Day / Week Levels'
NDOG_GROUP     = 'Opening Gaps (NDOG/NWOG)'

MAX_SESSION_BOXES  = 50
MAX_SESSION_LABELS = 50

MAX_ARRAY_SIZE       = 5000
MAX_STRUCTURE_LINES  = 200
MAX_STRUCTURE_LABELS = 200
MAX_SWING_LABELS     = 200
MAX_EQ_LINES         = 100
MAX_EQ_LABELS        = 100
MAX_ORDER_BLOCK_COUNT = 100
MAX_FVG_COUNT        = 100
MAX_BREAKER_COUNT    = 100
MAX_SWEEP_LABELS     = 100

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
modeInput                      = input.string(HISTORICAL, 'Mode',   group=SMART_GROUP, options=[HISTORICAL,PRESENT])
styleInput                     = input.string(COLORED,    'Style',  group=SMART_GROUP, options=[COLORED,MONOCHROME])
showTrendInput                 = input(false, 'Color Candles',       group=SMART_GROUP)
pivotSourceInput               = input.string('Body', 'Pivot Source', group=SMART_GROUP, options=['Body','Wick'], tooltip='Body = structure levels at candle bodies (filters wick sweeps from triggering BOS).\nWick = standard ICT swing definition (levels at actual highs/lows).')
showCEMidlinesInput            = input(true, 'Show CE Midlines (50%)', group=SMART_GROUP,
    tooltip='Draws a dotted midline at the 50% level (Consequent Encroachment) of Order Blocks and Breaker Blocks.\nFVG midpoint is already shown by the box split.\nThis is the optimal entry level in ICT methodology.')

showInternalsInput             = input(true,  'Show Internal Structure',   group=INTERNAL_GROUP)
showInternalBullInput          = input.string(ALL, 'Bullish Structure',    group=INTERNAL_GROUP, inline='ibull', options=[ALL,BOS,CHOCH])
internalBullColorInput         = input(GREEN, '',                          group=INTERNAL_GROUP, inline='ibull')
showInternalBearInput          = input.string(ALL, 'Bearish Structure',    group=INTERNAL_GROUP, inline='ibear', options=[ALL,BOS,CHOCH])
internalBearColorInput         = input(RED,   '',                          group=INTERNAL_GROUP, inline='ibear')
internalFilterConfluenceInput  = input(false, 'Confluence Filter',         group=INTERNAL_GROUP)
internalStructureSize          = input.string(TINY, 'Internal Label Size', group=INTERNAL_GROUP, options=[TINY,SMALL,NORMAL])
internalLengthInput            = input.int(5, 'Internal Swing Length',     group=INTERNAL_GROUP, minval=2, maxval=20, tooltip='Pivot lookback for internal structure.')

showStructureInput             = input(true,  'Show Swing Structure',      group=SWING_GROUP)
showSwingBullInput             = input.string(ALL, 'Bullish Structure',    group=SWING_GROUP, inline='bull', options=[ALL,BOS,CHOCH])
swingBullColorInput            = input(GREEN, '',                          group=SWING_GROUP, inline='bull')
showSwingBearInput             = input.string(ALL, 'Bearish Structure',    group=SWING_GROUP, inline='bear', options=[ALL,BOS,CHOCH])
swingBearColorInput            = input(RED,   '',                          group=SWING_GROUP, inline='bear')
swingStructureSize             = input.string(SMALL, 'Swing Label Size',   group=SWING_GROUP, options=[TINY,SMALL,NORMAL])
showSwingsInput                = input(false, 'Show Swing Points',         group=SWING_GROUP, inline='swings')
swingsLengthInput              = input.int(20, '',                         group=SWING_GROUP, minval=5, inline='swings', tooltip='Swing pivot lookback length.')
showHighLowSwingsInput         = input(true,  'Show Strong/Weak High/Low', group=SWING_GROUP)

showInternalOrderBlocksInput   = input(true,  'Internal Order Blocks',     group=BLOCKS_GROUP, inline='iob')
internalOrderBlocksSizeInput   = input.int(5, '',                          group=BLOCKS_GROUP, minval=1, maxval=20, inline='iob')
showSwingOrderBlocksInput      = input(false, 'Swing Order Blocks',        group=BLOCKS_GROUP, inline='ob')
swingOrderBlocksSizeInput      = input.int(5, '',                          group=BLOCKS_GROUP, minval=1, maxval=20, inline='ob')
orderBlockFilterInput          = input.string('Atr', 'OB Filter',          group=BLOCKS_GROUP, options=[ATR,RANGE])
orderBlockMitigationInput      = input.string(BODY_SRC, 'OB Mitigation',   group=BLOCKS_GROUP, options=[CLOSE_SRC,BODY_SRC,HIGHLOW],
    tooltip='Close = close must cross the OB level (strictest).\nBody = candle body must cross (ICT standard — filters wick sweeps).\nHigh/Low = any wick through the level counts (most aggressive).')
minPenetrationFactorInput      = input.float(0.1, 'Min Penetration xATR',  group=BLOCKS_GROUP, minval=0.0, maxval=1.0, step=0.05,
    tooltip='Minimum fraction of ATR required to penetrate the OB level for valid mitigation (filters marginal body clips).')
minPenetrationTicksInput       = input.float(0.0, 'Min Penetration Ticks', group=BLOCKS_GROUP, minval=0.0, step=1.0,
    tooltip='Absolute minimum tick penetration required (useful for low ATR conditions).')
orderBlockRangeInput           = input.string(FULL_CANDLE, 'OB Range',     group=BLOCKS_GROUP, options=[FULL_CANDLE,BODY_ONLY], tooltip='Full Candle = standard ICT (wicks included). Body Only = tighter zones.')
internalBullishOrderBlockColor = input.color(color.new(#3179f5,80), 'Internal Bull OB', group=BLOCKS_GROUP)
internalBearishOrderBlockColor = input.color(color.new(#f77c80,80), 'Internal Bear OB', group=BLOCKS_GROUP)
swingBullishOrderBlockColor    = input.color(color.new(#1848cc,80), 'Bullish OB',       group=BLOCKS_GROUP)
swingBearishOrderBlockColor    = input.color(color.new(#b22833,80), 'Bearish OB',       group=BLOCKS_GROUP)
showOBTouchCountInput          = input(true,  'Show Touch Count on OBs',   group=BLOCKS_GROUP)
maxOBTouchesInput              = input.int(3, 'Max Touches Before Exhaust', group=BLOCKS_GROUP,
    minval=1, maxval=10,
    tooltip='After this many discrete retests (outside→inside transitions), the Order Block (or Breaker Block) is removed as exhausted.\n1st touch = highest probability.')

showInternalBreakerBlocksInput   = input(false, 'Internal Breaker Blocks',  group=BREAKER_GROUP, inline='ibb')
internalBreakerBlocksSizeInput   = input.int(5, '',                         group=BREAKER_GROUP, minval=1, maxval=20, inline='ibb')
showSwingBreakerBlocksInput      = input(false, 'Swing Breaker Blocks',     group=BREAKER_GROUP, inline='bb')
swingBreakerBlocksSizeInput      = input.int(5, '',                         group=BREAKER_GROUP, minval=1, maxval=20, inline='bb',
     tooltip='When an Order Block is mitigated, it becomes a Breaker Block with flipped bias.\nBullish OB broken → Bearish Breaker (resistance)\nBearish OB broken → Bullish Breaker (support)\nOBs are tracked internally even if OB display is off.')
internalBullishBreakerColor      = input.color(color.new(#00bcd4,70), 'Internal Bull BB', group=BREAKER_GROUP)
internalBearishBreakerColor      = input.color(color.new(#ff9800,70), 'Internal Bear BB', group=BREAKER_GROUP)
swingBullishBreakerColor         = input.color(color.new(#00838f,70), 'Bullish BB',       group=BREAKER_GROUP)
swingBearishBreakerColor         = input.color(color.new(#e65100,70), 'Bearish BB',       group=BREAKER_GROUP)
showBBTouchCountInput            = input(true,  'Show Touch Count on BBs',  group=BREAKER_GROUP,
    tooltip='Display retest count on Breaker Blocks, independent of OB touch count toggle.')

showEqualHighsLowsInput        = input(true,   'Equal High/Low',           group=EQUAL_GROUP)
equalHighsLowsLengthInput      = input.int(3,  'Bars Confirmation',        group=EQUAL_GROUP, minval=1)
equalHighsLowsThresholdInput   = input.float(0.1, 'Threshold',             group=EQUAL_GROUP, minval=0, maxval=0.5, step=0.1)
equalHighsLowsSizeInput        = input.string(TINY, 'Label Size',          group=EQUAL_GROUP, options=[TINY,SMALL,NORMAL])

showFairValueGapsInput         = input(false, 'Fair Value Gaps',            group=GAPS_GROUP)
fairValueGapsThresholdInput    = input(true,  'Auto Threshold',             group=GAPS_GROUP)
fairValueGapsTimeframeInput    = input.timeframe('', 'Timeframe',           group=GAPS_GROUP)
fairValueGapsBullColorInput    = input.color(color.new(#00ff68,70), 'Bullish FVG', group=GAPS_GROUP)
fairValueGapsBearColorInput    = input.color(color.new(#ff0008,70), 'Bearish FVG', group=GAPS_GROUP)
fairValueGapsExtendInput       = input.int(1, 'Extend FVG',                group=GAPS_GROUP, minval=0)

showIFVGInput       = input(false, 'Show Inverted FVGs',       group=IFVG_GROUP,
    tooltip='When a FVG is fully mitigated, it flips bias and becomes an iFVG.\nBullish FVG filled → Bearish iFVG (resistance).\nBearish FVG filled → Bullish iFVG (support).')
ifvgBullColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#00bcd4, 75), 'Bullish iFVG', group=IFVG_GROUP)
ifvgBearColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#ff9800, 75), 'Bearish iFVG', group=IFVG_GROUP)
ifvgMaxCountInput   = input.int(10, 'Max iFVGs Shown',        group=IFVG_GROUP, minval=1, maxval=50)
ifvgMitigationInput = input.string(BODY_SRC, 'iFVG Mitigation', group=IFVG_GROUP, options=[CLOSE_SRC,BODY_SRC,HIGHLOW],
    tooltip='Close = close must invalidate the iFVG level.\nBody = candle body must invalidate the level.\nHigh/Low = any wick through the level invalidates it.')

showDailyLevelsInput           = input(false, 'Daily',   group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='daily')
dailyLevelsStyleInput          = input.string(SOLID, '', group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='daily',   options=[SOLID,DASHED,DOTTED])
dailyLevelsColorInput          = input(BLUE, '',         group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='daily')
showWeeklyLevelsInput          = input(false, 'Weekly',  group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='weekly')
weeklyLevelsStyleInput         = input.string(SOLID, '', group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='weekly',  options=[SOLID,DASHED,DOTTED])
weeklyLevelsColorInput         = input(BLUE, '',         group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='weekly')
showMonthlyLevelsInput         = input(false, 'Monthly', group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='monthly')
monthlyLevelsStyleInput        = input.string(SOLID, '', group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='monthly', options=[SOLID,DASHED,DOTTED])
monthlyLevelsColorInput        = input(BLUE, '',         group=LEVELS_GROUP, inline='monthly')

showPremiumDiscountZonesInput  = input(false, 'Premium/Discount Zones', group=ZONES_GROUP)
premiumZoneColorInput          = input.color(RED,   'Premium Zone',      group=ZONES_GROUP)
equilibriumZoneColorInput      = input.color(GRAY,  'Equilibrium Zone',  group=ZONES_GROUP)
discountZoneColorInput         = input.color(GREEN, 'Discount Zone',     group=ZONES_GROUP)
useTrailResetInput             = input(false, 'Reset Range on Trend Change', group=ZONES_GROUP,
    tooltip='ON = tight OTE/zones (resets trailing top/bottom on swing trend flip).\nOFF = wide expanding range (default behavior).\nAffects Premium/Discount Zones, OTE Zone, and Strong/Weak High/Low.')

showLiquiditySweepsInput       = input(false, 'Liquidity Sweeps',         group=SWEEP_GROUP)
sweepBullColorInput            = input.color(GREEN, 'Bullish Sweep Color', group=SWEEP_GROUP)
sweepBearColorInput            = input.color(RED,   'Bearish Sweep Color', group=SWEEP_GROUP)
sweepLabelSizeInput            = input.string(TINY, 'Sweep Label Size',    group=SWEEP_GROUP, options=[TINY,SMALL,NORMAL])

showMSSInput          = input(true,  'Identify MSS (Displacement CHoCH)', group=MSS_GROUP,
    tooltip='When a CHoCH is confirmed by a displacement candle (large body, minimal wicks, direction matches), it is labelled MSS instead of CHoCH.\nMSS = higher conviction reversal signal.')
mssATRMultInput       = input.float(1.0, 'Displacement ATR Multiplier',   group=MSS_GROUP,
    minval=0.3, maxval=3.0, step=0.1,
    tooltip='Breakout candle body must exceed this × ATR to qualify as displacement.\n1.0 = body at least as large as average range.\nLower = more MSS signals. Higher = stricter filter.')
mssBodyRatioInput     = input.float(0.5, 'Min Body/Range Ratio',          group=MSS_GROUP,
    minval=0.2, maxval=0.9, step=0.05,
    tooltip='Minimum ratio of candle body to total range.\n0.5 = body is at least half the candle.\nHigher = cleaner candles only (less wick).')
mssDisplacementLookbackInput = input.int(3, 'MSS Displacement Lookback', group=MSS_GROUP,
    minval=1, maxval=10,
    tooltip='Number of recent bars that can qualify a CHoCH as MSS.\n3 preserves the original behavior.')
mssApplyInternalInput = input(true,  'Apply to Internal Structure',       group=MSS_GROUP)
mssApplySwingInput    = input(true,  'Apply to Swing Structure',          group=MSS_GROUP)
mssBullColorInput     = input.color(#00e676, 'Bullish MSS Color',         group=MSS_GROUP)
mssBearColorInput     = input.color(#ff1744, 'Bearish MSS Color',         group=MSS_GROUP)
showDisplacementInput = input(true, 'Highlight Displacement Candles', group=MSS_GROUP,
    tooltip='Places a marker on the candle whose displacement qualified the MSS.\nOnly appears when an MSS is confirmed.')

showOTEInput       = input(false, 'Show OTE Zone',              group=OTE_GROUP)
oteBullColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#00e676, 75), 'Bullish OTE', group=OTE_GROUP)
oteBearColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#ff1744, 75), 'Bearish OTE', group=OTE_GROUP)
showOTEFibsInput   = input(true,  'Show Fib Lines (50% / 61.8% / 78.6%)', group=OTE_GROUP,
    tooltip='OTE = 61.8%–78.6% Fibonacci retracement of the current swing range.\nBullish trend → buy zone in discount.\nBearish trend → sell zone in premium.')
oteFib1Input       = input.float(0.618, 'Fib Level 1 (Upper)', group=OTE_GROUP, minval=0.5, maxval=0.9, step=0.01)
oteFib2Input       = input.float(0.786, 'Fib Level 2 (Lower)', group=OTE_GROUP, minval=0.5, maxval=0.95, step=0.01)

showAsianRangeInput      = input(false, 'Show Asian Range H/L',  group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
asianRangeSessionInput   = input.string('2000-0000', 'Session Hours', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP,
    options=['1800-0000','1900-0000','2000-0000','2000-0100','2100-0200'],
    tooltip='Asian session hours in HHMM-HHMM format.\n2000-0000 = 20:00 to 00:00.\nAll times in the selected timezone.')
rangeTimezoneInput  = input.string('America/New_York', 'Range Timezone', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP,
    options=['America/New_York','America/Chicago','America/Los_Angeles',
            'Europe/London','Europe/Berlin','Asia/Tokyo','Asia/Hong_Kong',
            'Asia/Kolkata','Asia/Singapore','Australia/Sydney','UTC'])
asianRangeHighColorInput = input.color(color.new(#e040fb, 30), 'Asian High Color', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
asianRangeLowColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#e040fb, 30), 'Asian Low Color',  group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
asianRangeStyleInput     = input.string(DASHED, 'Line Style',    group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP, options=[SOLID,DASHED,DOTTED])

// ── London Range ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
showLondonRangeInput      = input(false, 'Show London Range H/L',  group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
londonRangeSessionInput   = input.string('0300-0830', 'London Session Hours', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP,
    options=['0200-0500','0300-0800','0300-0830','0300-1200'],
    tooltip='London session hours for range capture.\n0300-0830 = typical London open range before NY overlap.')
londonRangeHighColorInput = input.color(color.new(#2196f3, 30), 'London High Color', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
londonRangeLowColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#2196f3, 30), 'London Low Color',  group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
londonRangeStyleInput     = input.string(DASHED, 'London Line Style', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP, options=[SOLID,DASHED,DOTTED])

// ── New York Range ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
showNYRangeInput          = input(false, 'Show New York Range H/L', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
nyRangeSessionInput       = input.string('0800-1200', 'NY Session Hours', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP,
    options=['0700-1000','0800-1200','0800-1700','0930-1200'],
    tooltip='New York session hours for range capture.\n0800-1200 = NY open range before midday.')
nyRangeHighColorInput     = input.color(color.new(#ff9800, 30), 'NY High Color', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
nyRangeLowColorInput      = input.color(color.new(#ff9800, 30), 'NY Low Color',  group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP)
nyRangeStyleInput         = input.string(DASHED, 'NY Line Style', group=ASIANRANGE_GROUP, options=[SOLID,DASHED,DOTTED])

showKillZonesInput      = input(false, 'Show Kill Zones',              group=KILLZONE_GROUP)
kzAsianInput            = input(true,  'Asian KZ (20:00–00:00)',       group=KILLZONE_GROUP, inline='kza')
kzAsianColorInput       = input.color(color.new(#9c27b0, 88), '',     group=KILLZONE_GROUP, inline='kza')
kzLondonOpenInput       = input(true,  'London Open KZ (02:00–05:00)',group=KILLZONE_GROUP, inline='kzl')
kzLondonOpenColorInput  = input.color(color.new(#ff9800, 88), '',     group=KILLZONE_GROUP, inline='kzl')
